    "text": "COVID-19 precautions and policies are in place to ensure the health and safety of our campus community. Information can be found on our main COVID-19 page\nApply\nVisit Campus\nRequest Info\nGive\nForesterNet\nSearch\nMenu\nWinter Break is Near\nClasses have finished and exam season is upon us! Make sure you rest between study sessions, Foresters. Winter break is just around the corner.\n1\n2\n3\nBring us your talents and passions, your curiosity and your drive, and we'll give you the tools you need to build your dream career.\nMake Yourself Known. Make Your Own Way. Make It Personal. \nAcademics\nChicago\nCareers\nAdmissions\nStudent Life\nAthletics\nAPPLY\nVISIT CAMPUS\nREQUEST INFORMATION\nSCHOLARSHIPS\n#3\nBEST\nHealth Services\nThe Princeton Review\n#4\nBEST\nScience Lab Facilities\nThe Princeton Review\n#16\nBEST\nValue College\nU.S. News & World Report\n#85\nFOR\nBest National Liberal Arts Colleges\nU.S. News & World Report\nMaking sense of financial aid and the value of a college education\nHigher education is an investment in the future, but sometimes, knowing where to start with financial aid can be a challenge. Understanding financial aid can help reduce the uncertainty surrounding the value of a degree. Read our comprehensive guide to funding your education so you feel confident as you explore education options. \nLEARN MORE\nNEWS\nVIEW ALL NEWS\nDECEMBER 06, 2022\nProfessors, alumna attend American Academy of Religion meeting in Colorado\nDECEMBER 02, 2022\nChicago Tribune turns to Ahmad Sadri for input on World Cup\nDECEMBER 01, 2022\nStudent attends Paris Peace Forum, meets world leaders\nNOVEMBER 22, 2022\nStudents present research at international neuroscience conference\nEVENTS\nEVENTS\nNOV 2022\n15\nfrom: The 27th Annual John and Katherine Covington Memorial Art Exhibition\nDEC 2022\n07\nResume Basics Workshop - December\nDEC 2022\n07\nGreenhouse Study Break\nNotes From Abroad\nCindy Landaeta Farias '24 shares her experiences from France\nCindy Landaeta Farias '24, a double major in Philosophy and International Relations with a minor in French, is studying abroad at Institut d'Etudes Politiques de Rennes in France.\nREAD MORE\nExplore Our Career Pathways \nExplore your options through our four-year Career Pathways program. Through four stages of personal exploration and career development, you’ll make connections with people who can help you land a job or go to graduate school.\nCAREERS\nAlumni Online Community\nOur powerful alumni network is an invaluable resource. Stay connected, get involved, and support our Foresters! \nLEARN MORE\nVirtual Campus Tour\n555 North Sheridan Road\nLake Forest, Illinois 60045\n847-234-3100\nAdmissions: 847-735-5000\nApply\nVisit Campus\nRequest Information\nPrivacy\n© 2022 Lake Forest College\nConsumer Information\nNon-Discrimination Policy\nAccessibility\nEmergency Information\nDirections to Lake Forest College",
